    • Method Detail

      • getRequireWiFiForAudio

        boolean getRequireWiFiForAudio()
        Gets whether audio should only work when on Wi-Fi. The default value is false. Any network connection can be used for audio. Note: even if set to allow any network connection, server policy may prevent this.
        Returns:
        boolean true if wi-fi is required for audio, false otherwise.

      • setRequireWiFiForAudio

        void setRequireWiFiForAudio(boolean requireWiFiForAudio)
        Sets whether audio should only work when on Wi-Fi
        Parameters:
        requireWiFiForAudio - true if Wi-Fi connection is required, false otherwise.

      • getRequireWiFiForVideo

        boolean getRequireWiFiForVideo()
        Gets whether video should only work when on Wi-Fi. The default value is true. Wi-Fi is required for video. Note: even if set to allow any network connection, server policy may prevent this.
        Returns:
        boolean true if wi-fi is required for video, false otherwise.

      • setRequireWiFiForVideo

        void setRequireWiFiForVideo(boolean requireWiFiForVideo)
        Sets whether video should only work when on Wi-Fi
        Parameters:
        requireWiFiForVideo - true Wi-Fi connection is desired, false otherwise.

      • enablePreviewFeatures

        void enablePreviewFeatures(boolean enablePreviewFeatures)
        If set, certain preview features will be enabled in the SDK. E.g. For OnPrem topologies, setting this flag to true will enable Audio/Video call flows. This flag should be set immediately after you get the application instance.
        Parameters:
        enablePreviewFeatures - Enables preview features.

      • setMaxVideoChannelCount

        void setMaxVideoChannelCount(long maxVideoChannelCount)
        This property should be used to set the max available video channels to view the video stream of multiple participants in the meeting. The request may be effectively capped by platform static or runtime limit. If number of participants sending video is greater than this limit, the most active participants will offer a subscription. Follow the ParticipantVideo.canSubscribe changes.
        Parameters:
        maxVideoChannelCount - Maximum number of video channels.
        See Also:
        ParticipantVideo

      • getMaxVideoChannelCount

        long getMaxVideoChannelCount()
        Returns the maximum available video channel count.
        Returns:
        Maximum available video channel count.

      • setEndUserAcceptedVideoLicense

        void setEndUserAcceptedVideoLicense()
        Notify that user has accepted the video license. This is required to proceed with features that potentially use H.264 codec. Until this method is called, any attempt to use those features will fail.
        See Also:
        ErrorCode.E_VIDEOLICENSENOTACCEPTED
